On 6 July 2023 2:34:50 pm IST, Andreas Tille  wrote:
>last time we were wondering whether a monthly video meeting is more
>sensible.  Its not that much we need to talk about (in case there is
>something we can perfectly do ad hoc meetings) and may be its enough to
>meet only once a month.  If we want to switch to a monthly period, do we
>want to meet a a certain day of the week (say Friday or Sunday) or do we
>want to meet say at each 17th of a month to move over all weekdays which
>will not exclude somebody who might not be able to join at a certain day
>of the week.

For me, it isn't about the frequency but about the day and the time. The 18:00 UTC translates to a weird time in my TZ, and on mid of the week working days, joining at that time is simply not feasible.

I'm okay with whatever frequency you decide (monthly or once in two weeks) but please take into account the time and the day. With the strategy you propose, I'd likely be able to join once in 7 months :)

I'd suggest to have a poll, instead with different dates and times.

Best,
Nilesh
